external_knowledge:
completed sales refers to properties where the sale has been finalized and ownership has been transferred; 
property type refers to categories or classifications of properties (e.g., residential, commercial, industrial); 
neighborhoods are geographical areas within a city or town; 
overall ranking indicates how a neighborhood ranks relative to other neighborhoods across different property types.

sql:
SELECT AVG(value_value) AS average_number_of_properties
FROM neighborhood_values
WHERE value_name = 'number of properties';

external_knowledge:
- "Recently sold properties" refers to properties with a sale status of 'completed' within the last year; 
- "Characteristics" include property type, use code, area, year built, and Z-index value; 
- "Neighborhood information" includes the neighborhood name and population density; 
- "Features and values" are aggregated summaries of various property attributes (e.g., number of bedrooms, finished square feet); 
- "Access history by analysts" includes the name of the analyst, the number of times they accessed the property, and the average days since their last access.

- A "recently listed property" refers to a property listed within the last six months; 
- "Single-family property" is a type of property, as indicated by the usecode 'SingleFamily'; 
- A "spacious property" refers to a property with an area greater than the average size of its property type.
